<subSubSection id="2BFA651DE822FFCA5BF4FF09BF71FD76" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="635F3696E822FFCA5BF4FF09BC1AFE56" blockId="19.[151,1437,151,681]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
DNA barcode analyses group 
<taxonomicName id="A4E04D15E822FFCA5928FF09BCA9FF6E" baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1782" box="[539,729,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Pyropteron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysidiformis">
<emphasis id="5194EA84E822FFCA5928FF09BCA9FF6E" box="[539,729,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. chrysidiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into two distinct clusters, which differ by an average of 6.8%, the 
<taxonomicName id="A4E04D15E822FFCA5BF3FF25BF12FF0A" baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1782" box="[192,354,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Pyropteron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysidiformis">
<emphasis id="5194EA84E822FFCA5BF3FF25BF12FF0A" box="[192,354,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">chrysidiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade, with specimens from western Europe, including north-western 
<collectingCountry id="1BF77606E822FFCA5F5DFF25BAD2FF0A" box="[1134,1186,187,213]" name="Italy" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="1BF77606E822FFCA5F9EFF25BB73FF0A" box="[1197,1283,187,213]" name="France" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Corsica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingRegion id="A124F874E822FFCA5E0BFF25BBE8FF0A" box="[1336,1432,187,213]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
, and the 
<emphasis id="5194EA84E822FFCA5BC0FF41BF46FF26" box="[243,310,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">sicula</emphasis>
clade with specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="A124F874E822FFCA594AFF41BCCBFF26" box="[633,699,223,249]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Sicily</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="A124F874E822FFCA59F4FF41BD66FF26" box="[711,790,223,249]" country="Italy" name="Puglia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Apulia</collectingRegion>
, Adriatic 
<collectingCountry id="1BF77606E822FFCA58B5FF41BDC9FF26" box="[902,953,223,249]" name="Italy" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Italy</collectingCountry>
and Istria. These two clades are well supported and could be considered different species. However, although there are some external differences between specimens of the two clades, these were not consistent across the whole range and we did not find significant differences in the genitalia. We therefore follow the current practise (
<bibRefCitation id="07714B67E822FFCA584EFED2BA17FEBA" author="Spatenka, K. &amp; Gorbunov, O. &amp; Lastuvka, Z. &amp; Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y." box="[893,1127,331,359]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref61296" refString="Spatenka, K., Gorbunov, O., Lastuvka, Z., Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y. (1999) s. n. In: Naumann, C. (Ed.), Handbook of Palaearctic Macrolepidoptera. Vol. 1. Sesiidae - Clearwing Moths. Gem Publishing Company, Wallingford, pp. 1 - 569." type="book" year="1999">
Špatenka 
<emphasis id="5194EA84E822FFCA58DEFED5BA55FEBA" box="[1005,1061,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="07714B67E822FFCA5F41FED5BBE5FEBA" author="Puhringer, F. &amp; Kallies, A." box="[1138,1429,331,357]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref60344" refString="Puhringer, F. &amp; Kallies, A. (2004) Provisional check list of the Sesiidae of the world (Lepidoptera: Ditrysia). Mitteilungen der Entomologischen Arbeitsgemeinschaft Salzkammergut, 4, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="2004">Pühringer &amp; Kallies 2004</bibRefCitation>
) and consider these two clades subspecies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="635F3696E822FFCA5BF4FE0DBF71FD76" blockId="19.[151,1437,151,681]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="5194EA84E822FFCA5BF4FE0DBF76FE72" bold="true" box="[199,262,403,429]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Note.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A4E04D15E822FFCA5A3CFE0DBC3EFE72" authority="Oberthur, 1909" authorityName="Oberthur" authorityYear="1909" box="[271,590,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Sesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lecerfi">
<emphasis id="5194EA84E822FFCA5A3CFE0DBFEAFE72" box="[271,410,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Sesia lecerfi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="07714B67E822FFCA5A90FE0DBC3EFE72" author="Oberthur, C." box="[419,590,403,429]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="186 - 187" refId="ref59988" refString="Oberthur, C. (1909) Description d'une espece nouvelle francaise de Sesia [Lep. Het.]. Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France, 10, 186 - 187." type="journal article" year="1909">Oberthür, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is not a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="A4E04D15E822FFCA5870FE0DBA72FE72" baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1782" box="[835,1026,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Pyropteron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysidiformis">
<emphasis id="5194EA84E822FFCA5870FE0DBA72FE72" box="[835,1026,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. chrysidiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with which it was compared in the original description and as proposed by subsequent authors (
<bibRefCitation id="07714B67E822FFCA5870FE28BD8BFE0E" author="Lastuvka, Z." box="[835,1019,438,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="129 - 132" refId="ref58703" refString="Lastuvka, Z. (1990 c [1989]) Zur Taxonomie von Synansphecia triannuliformis (Freyer, 1845). Acta Unversitatis Agriculturae, 37 (3 - 4), 129 - 132." type="journal article" year="1990">Laštůvka 1990c</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="07714B67E822FFCA5F34FE26BA83FE0E" author="Spatenka, K. &amp; Gorbunov, O. &amp; Lastuvka, Z. &amp; Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y." box="[1031,1267,439,467]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref61296" refString="Spatenka, K., Gorbunov, O., Lastuvka, Z., Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y. (1999) s. n. In: Naumann, C. (Ed.), Handbook of Palaearctic Macrolepidoptera. Vol. 1. Sesiidae - Clearwing Moths. Gem Publishing Company, Wallingford, pp. 1 - 569." type="book" year="1999">
Špatenka 
<emphasis id="5194EA84E822FFCA5F45FE29BADFFE0E" box="[1142,1199,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus id="BC5B8834E822FFCA5E09FE29BBECFE0E" box="[1338,1436,439,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
from the Eastern Pyrenees is an almost completely black male of a 
<taxonomicName id="A4E04D15E822FFCA589BFE45BA08FE2A" box="[936,1144,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="5194EA84E822FFCA589BFE45BA66FE2A" box="[936,1046,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Bembecia</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
Due to the shapes of the transparent areas of the forewing, the relatively large size with an alar expanse of 
<quantity id="A4189B73E822FFCA5F14FE61BA06FDC6" box="[1063,1142,511,537]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 mm</quantity>
and the dark red colour of the forewing discal spot and anal margin (yellow or orange-red in most congeners), we consider it most likely to be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="A4E04D15E822FFCA5A66FDD9BCE4FDBE" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[341,660,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ichneumoniformis">
<emphasis id="5194EA84E822FFCA5A66FDD9BCE4FDBE" box="[341,660,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Bembecia ichneumoniformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
([Denis &amp; Schiffermüller], 1775) and synonymize it with this species (
<emphasis id="5194EA84E822FFCA5B92FDF5BF79FD5A" bold="true" box="[161,265,619,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">syn. nov.</emphasis>
). However, this issue needs to be re-addressed by examination of the genitalia or DNA-analysis of the 
<typeStatus id="BC5B8834E822FFCA5BA4FD11BE8DFD76" box="[151,253,655,681]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
